<section class="hero">

<h1>
Epi<span>genomics</span>
</h1>

<p>
Epigenomics investigates the chemical modifications and chromatin states that regulate gene activity without altering the DNA sequence. By studying DNA methylation, histone modifications, chromatin accessibility, and regulatory landscapes, epigenomics reveals how cells control identity, development, disease, and environmental response.
</p>

<div class="hero-image">
  <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>
    <source src="/3_Epigennomics.mp4" type="video/mp4">
  </video>
</div>

</section>

<section class="section">

<h2>
What is <span>Epigenomics?</span>
</h2>

<div class="infographic">

  <img
    src="/1_Epigennomics.png"
    alt="Epigenomics overview infographic"
  >

</div>

<p>
Epigenomics is the study of genome-wide regulatory marks and chromatin features that influence gene activity without changing the underlying DNA sequence.
</p>

<p>
Modern epigenomics uses sequencing technologies, chromatin profiling, DNA methylation analysis, and computational biology to understand cellular identity, development, aging, cancer, and environmental response.
</p>

