<h2>
Epigenomics and <span>Omics Sciences</span>
</h2>

<p>
Epigenomics connects genomic information to gene regulation by revealing how chromatin structure and chemical modifications influence whether genes are active, silent, or dynamically controlled.
</p>

<p>
At PanorOmics, epigenomics is a critical regulatory layer that links genomics, transcriptomics, environmental exposure, aging, cancer biology, and precision medicine.
</p>

